 to Brother Vresk</span><hr size=1> A folded letter of fine illweed parchment from Kunark lies in the middle of the bridge over the river in Nektulos. The fine blood ink casts a soft red glow that can be seen from a distance. It is obvious that this letter wants to be found.<br>
The first half of the letter is written in the common tongue, and reads:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> To the finder of this letter,<br>
     This note has been placed in your world through powerful magics. Please deliver this message to Brother Vresk of the Violent Harvest. Tell him where you found it so he will be able to reply. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The rest of the letter is written in the language of the Iksar:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dear Brother Vresk,<br>
     I have given this note to a researcher in the Tower of Death in our city of Cabilis. Through his research, he has discovered worlds much like ours, with small differences. Grandmaster Glox invited him to the Court of Pain and asked him to search for a disciple of the Swiftails in one of the other worlds. We found you. We noticed that you are allowed to walk freely in the Teir`Dal city. In our world, the Teir`Dal are our brothers in arms, yet they will not allow us in their city. We are interested in learning the method you acquired their permission to enter in detail. It is important for young Swiftails of Cabilis to have another safe haven. I am writing this letter as Glox is too busy with his meditations to do so himself. Please write us a response letter. You can return it to my world by placing it, with this note, back at the place where it appeared in your world. Your service to the Swiftails shall be reported to the Emperor and Prime Hierophant Vek in case you ever find yourself lost and without a home in my world. Thank you.<br>
                                                 Brother Xakshiak Sserikak,<br>
                                                 Disciple of Cazic-Thule<br>
                                                 (Tallon Zek)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uvresk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vresk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ambassador to Kunark</span><br>  Posts: 334<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 8:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A letter addressed to Brother Vresk</span><hr size=1> A responding letter is found:<br>
<br>
Dark tidings, Brother.  It is not often one is able to speak to ones counterpart in an alternate plane of existance.  I trust this will find you the same as your message found me.<br>
<br>
The method for being accepted to most of Neriak is fairly easy.  You will need an ally for the first part.  One who can cast invisibility upon you.<br>
<br>
First, buy several stacks of red wine.  An entire backpack full will do nicely.  You may find this is a bit much, just donate the extras to some allies for later use. Then, under the cloak of invisibility, head to the library located in Neriak Third Gate.<br>
<br>
Once inside the library, there is a long Teir'Dal researcher by the name of Lokar Tobiath.  He is a necromancer of approximately 12 seasons, and should not attack you on sight.  This necromancer has an uncommonly fond taste for red wine.  Giving him mass quantities of it (4 at a time) will improve your standings with the Dread Guard Inner, Outer, and the Dark Bargainers.  The Dark Bargainers are the merchants of Neriak by the way.<br>
<br>
Lokar is a bit picky at first though.  You'll find that he will not accept your gift of wine without some help at first.  What you need to do is give him the wine (open up the trade window), then have your friend cast invisibility upon you before you finalize your deal (have invis cast on you while the trade window is open (you must have another do this for you, as you cannot activate items while the window is open, and invis falls when you open a trade window) then have the friend invis you before you hit the trade button).  Your standings with the dark bargainers will go up especially fast (within a stack you won't need your friend anymore).<br>
<br>
You may note that this does not improve faction with the entire city.  However, with few exceptions you will be able to travel freely in the city as long as you avoid going into the various guilds.<br>
<br>
One notable exception to this rule are the wandering guards in Third Gate.  A good portion of these are actually not on the Dread Guard faction, but the priest's faction.  This faction took me a good long while to find a way to improve.  Should you have need of this particular faction, let me know.  Otherwise, the instructions I have given should be sufficient for banking and trading purposes. <p><img src=http://starwave.smartdesk.net/www/kooK/vresk1.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=334.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=334.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=1><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/harvest/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=334.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.threadControl?topicID=334.topic><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/harvest/skull.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=334.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=334.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to st